    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "TWA\n11011\nTRANS WORLD",
      "TRANS WORLD AIRLINES\nLockheed L-1011 Dash 100\nIntroduced on its routes in 1972, TWA now operates one of\nthe largest L-1011 fleets in the world. The L-1011-100 is an\nimproved, longer range model of the popular TriStar, operat-\ning principally on Transatlantic routes. It has a sophisticated\ninertial navigation system, and can fly and land completely\nautomatically in \"zero ceiling\" weather; the only wide-body\nairliner with such capabilities.\nPublished by Aviation World, Inc., P.O. Box 188, Bethel, Conn. 06801 U.S.A.\nL-026\n77071-D\npost card\nPhoto courtesy Lockheed-California Company\nN31033 c/n 1221\n2002. 113.488"
    ],
